					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Well I was thinking each tile would just have its own BB, so you work out what tile you are on, which way you are moving and then check against the right tiles, where if the tile is solid you check against the expanded box for the tile. <br />Having two points means you need to rotate said two points, so having a middle + 2 offsets. However thinking about it more said rotation can just be a LUT, to which doing the base + delta &gt; tile check tile x2 probably works out much of a muchness vs the oversampling of the other method..</div>

